# Vector Search Tools (MnemoVector MCP)

When semantic search is enabled, these MCP tools are available:

## Tools
- `vector_search` — semantic search across all indexed memory
- `vector_sync` — re-index changed files into the vector store
- `vector_forget` — remove a file from the vector index
- `vector_health` — check index health and stats
- `memory_status` — overview of memory system state

## Usage
1. Run `vector_health` to verify the vector store is healthy
2. Run `vector_sync` to build/update the index
3. Use `vector_search` with natural language queries

## Fallback
If vector search is unavailable, keep using:
- `scripts/memory/query-memory.sh --query "..."`
- `scripts/memory/query-memory.sh --query "..." --use-sqlite`
